  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "FINANCE MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>JOB DESCRIPTION :</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform financial management duties including generating financial data, compiling and submitting reports, analyzing industry trends and assessing the financial health of the company.</li>\n  <li>Oversee the operations and development of the company’s finance departments including creating and reviewing policies, budgeting, recruiting, training and conducting regular assessments of financial procedures.</li>\n  <li>Supervise the preparation of quarterly and annual account reconciliations, monitor and enforce compliance with tax and financial reporting standards and assist with cash flow forecasting of daily finance activities.</li>\n  <li>Advise colleagues and executive management on decisions related to the company’s finances and accounts.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop, maintain and update cost accounting models and systems, standard costs to advise management on price changes in order to maintain and maximize profit margins</li>\n  <li>Lead the development, roll-up and communication of inventory planning activities</li>\n  <li>Conduct research and data analysis to inform business decisions</li>\n  <li>Analyze industry trends, identify expansion opportunities and competitive threats in the market</li>\n  <li>Monitor the day-to-day financial operations within the company</li>\n  <li>Prepare and present periodic financial forecast and results to the Managing Director.</li>\n  <li>Provide strategic recommendations to the management team and advising on long-term business and financial planning</li>\n  <li>Responsible for ensuring the risk and compliance management framework is embedded and operational for the Company</li>\n  <li>Advise operational leaders on financial, strategic, organizational, and business issues for both short- and long-term growth strategies.</li>\n  <li>Assist in implementation of management and administrative financial systems, policies, and procedures to provide structure and discipline for sustained business growth.</li>\n  <li>Manage &amp; liaise with external auditor/tax agent</li>\n  <li>Perform other duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>REQUIREMENTS</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Accountancy, Finance, CPA, ACCA or its other equivalent</li>\n  <li>Strong technical accounting skills.</li>\n  <li>Good business sense and acumen</li>\n  <li>Strong analytical and numeracy skills, and able to work with minimum supervision</li>\n  <li>Ability to identify financial issues, develop and execute mitigating actions.</li>\n</ul>",
